---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Licensing & Guidelines";
const description =
    "Photographer Credit & Licensing Guidelines for using my work.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title}>
    <article class="guidelines-content">
        <header class="page-header">
            <h1>Photographer Credit & Licensing Guidelines</h1>
            <div class="meta-info">
                <p><strong>Abodid Sahoo</strong></p>
                <p>
                    <a href="https://abodid.com">abodid.com</a> | Instagram: <a
                        href="https://instagram.com/abodid.sahoo"
                        >@abodid.sahoo</a
                    > | LinkedIn: <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/abodidsahoo"
                        >Abodid Sahoo</a>
                </p>
            </div>
        </header>

        <p class="intro">
            These photographs capture live art events and exhibitions with an
            artistic vision. They go beyond documentation, offering creative
            interpretations that highlight both the artwork and the atmosphere.
            <br /><br />
            This page exists to ensure mutual respect, fair compensation, and long-term
            recognition of my work.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <section>
            <h2>How to Use This Page</h2>
            <p class="subtitle">Roadmap for Clients & Collaborators</p>
            <p>
                If you plan to use, publish, exhibit, license, or monetize my
                photographs, please read in this order:
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Credit & Ownership</strong> → Who must be credited and
                    what never changes
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Licensing & Usage Scope</strong> → What you are allowed
                    to do with the images
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Fees & Monetization</strong> → When payment is required
                    and how pricing works
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Use-Case Sections</strong> → Social, exhibitions, media,
                    research, print sales
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Ethics & Original Artists</strong> → Respect for collaborators
                    and creators
                </li>
            </ol>
            <p>
                <em
                    >If anything is unclear, usage must be discussed before
                    publication.</em>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>1. Credit & Ownership (Always Applies)</h2>

            <h3>Copyright</h3>
            <p>All photographs remain my copyright.</p>

            <h3>Credit name</h3>
            <p>Abodid Sahoo</p>

            <h3>Collaboration formats</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Artist × Abodid Sahoo</li>
                <li>Photo by Abodid Sahoo (Collaborator)</li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                <strong
                    >Credits must be clear and visible (captions, tags, labels).</strong>
            </p>
            <p>
                I do not transfer ownership of images. Usage is granted only
                through licensing.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>2. Licensing Principles (How Usage Is Defined)</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Non-exclusive licenses are offered by default.</li>
                <li>
                    Exclusive or commercial use requires a contract and fee.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Usage must be clearly defined by purpose, duration, and
                    platform.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Any use beyond the agreed scope requires additional
                    permission.
                </li>
                <li>
                    I do not grant open-ended, perpetual, or unrestricted usage
                    without written agreement.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>3. Fees & Monetization Overview</h2>
            <div class="fee-guide">
                <h3>Fee guide:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Editorial:</strong> from £150 / image</li>
                    <li><strong>Exhibitions:</strong> from £500</li>
                    <li><strong>Print sales:</strong> 50% split</li>
                    <li><strong>Commercial use:</strong> custom pricing</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <p>
                If an image generates revenue, promotes a brand, or is used
                beyond documentation, fees must be discussed.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>4. Use-Case Guidelines</h2>

            <h3>A. Online & Social Media</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Tag <a href="https://instagram.com/abodid.sahoo"
                        >@abodid.sahoo</a
                    > on Instagram.
                </li>
                <li>Credit Abodid Sahoo in captions.</li>
                <li>Link to abodid.com if online.</li>
                <li>Tag on LinkedIn if applicable.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>B. Exhibitions & Public Display</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Prior permission is mandatory for exhibition use.</li>
                <li>Fee varies by exhibition size.</li>
                <li>
                    This is artistic collaboration, not event photography.
                    Credit and exhibition materials must reflect this.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                <strong>Credit format:</strong><br />
                Photography by Abodid Sahoo (Collaborator)<br />
                [Artist] × Abodid Sahoo
            </p>

            <h3>C. Books, Magazines & Media</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Full credit required.</li>
                <li>Discuss fees if monetized.</li>
                <li>Contributor bio appreciated.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>D. Research & Academic Use</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Credit required.</li>
                <li>Contact me if a photo is key to research or patents.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>E. Prints, Sales & Monetization</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Prints must be sold through me. No unauthorized sales.</li>
                <li>
                    Be transparent. I would like to discuss the split of profits
                    if you handle print and marketing.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>5. Ethics, Fair Use & Respect for Original Artists</h2>
            <p>
                These photographs were taken at open public exhibitions where
                consent is generally implied. I respect the original artists and
                creators and:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Do not misrepresent their work in my images.</li>
                <li>Encourage credit to original artists alongside my own.</li>
                <li>
                    Am open to discussions or requests to remove images if
                    someone expresses discomfort.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>6. Working Together: What to Check</h2>
            <p>
                Before publishing, exhibiting, selling, or sharing my
                photographs, please confirm:
            </p>
            <ul class="checklist">
                <li>
                    <strong>Credit:</strong> Is my name displayed correctly and visibly?
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Usage Scope:</strong> Is the image being used only for
                    the agreed purpose?
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Monetization:</strong> Is the work generating revenue
                    or promotion? If yes, has a fee been agreed?
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Duration & Platforms:</strong> Is the usage limited to
                    specific formats, channels, or timeframes?
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Artists & Ethics:</strong> Are original creators credited
                    where appropriate?
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                If any answer is uncertain, please contact me before proceeding.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>7. Final Notes & Contact</h2>
            <p>
                This document exists to ensure mutual respect, fair
                compensation, and proper long-term recognition of my work.
            </p>
            <div class="contact-box">
                <p>
                    <strong
                        >For collaboration, licensing, prints, or usage
                        discussions:</strong>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Email: <a href="mailto:hello@abodid.com"
                        >hello@abodid.com</a>
                </p>
                <p>Website: <a href="https://abodid.com">abodid.com</a></p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .guidelines-content {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        font-family: var(--font-sans);
        color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    .page-header {
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .meta-info {
        margin-top: 1rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .meta-info a {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .intro {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    hr {
        border: 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
        margin: 3rem 0;
    }

    section {
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    h3 {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .subtitle {
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    ul,
    ol {
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .fee-guide {
        background: var(--bg-surface);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
    }

    .fee-guide h3 {
        margin-top: 0;
    }

    .checklist li {
        padding-left: 0.5rem;
    }

    .contact-box {
        background: var(--bg-surface);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--text-primary);
        margin-top: 1rem;
    }
</style>
